parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pump bracket can cause the power steering pump to malfunction, leading to loss of steering control, accidents, and vehicle damage.
symptoms: The power steering pump bracket breaks
the power steering pump fails
the serpentine belt breaks
fluid leaks
and the vehicle becomes difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie rod can cause the vehicle to lose steering control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The tie rod rips out of the frame
the vehicle becomes difficult to steer
and the driver may lose control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to restrain the occupant
the lap belt does not hold
and the occupant may be ejected from the seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column bolt can cause the steering column to become loose, leading to loss of steering control and accidents.
symptoms: The steering column bolt becomes loose
the steering column shifts
and the driver may have difficulty shifting gears and using turn signals.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can compromise the safety of the occupants in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor does not tighten up when pulled forward and backward
the seat belt buckle will not lock
the seat belt retractor gets stuck in a fixed position
broken parts jamming the retractor mechanism.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty seat track and frame can cause the seat to lift up and not stay secured, which can lead to accidents or injuries, especially during sudden stops or turns.
symptoms: The seat lifts up
does not stay secured to the track
and may cause discomfort or distraction while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The broken door handle can cause injuries to the driver or passengers, and make it difficult to enter or exit the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: The door handle breaks off
causing injury to the driver or passengers
and making it difficult to open or close the door.
